# Privacy Policy

Effective date: 2026-02-22

Simple URL Extractor does not collect, sell, or transmit personal data.

## What data is stored
The extension stores only user-defined extraction settings (optional start marker and end marker) in Chrome sync storage (`chrome.storage.sync`).

## How data is used
Stored settings are used only to improve URL extraction behavior on the user's browser.

## Data transmission
The extension does not send user data, browsing content, or extracted URLs to any remote server.

## Third-party sharing
No user data is shared with third parties.

## Permissions
- `contextMenus`: add the right-click extraction command.
- `activeTab` and `scripting`: show an in-page URL chooser only after user action.
- `storage`: save optional extraction markers.

## Data retention and control
Users can clear extension data at any time by removing the extension or resetting settings.

